        "title": "feat: add controlled catalog taxonomy and topics",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add separate controlled skill and plugin category slug registries using single-concept labels\n- accept author categories/topics through CLI and UI publish/edit surfaces; otherwise preserve stored values, infer controlled categories, then use `other`\n- ignore taxonomy declarations in `metadata.openclaw.json` and `openclaw.plugin.json`; plugin manifests remain inputs only for automatic contribution-slot inference\n- add exact-topic search, profile grouping, official-first category browse, and full-width mobile filter rows\n\n## Rollout dependency\n- capability tags are assumed removed independently and are not taxonomy inputs\n- existing legacy package category digests are intentionally not compatibility-mapped here; the corpus classification/backfill is PR 2 and must populate the new slugs before taxonomy browse is treated as corpus-complete\n\n## Proof\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit` (3,307 passed, 1 skipped)\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n- focused skill/plugin publish, metadata-source, taxonomy, digest, and import regression suites\n- real-browser 390x844 skills/plugins filter proof: zero same-line category rows and no horizontal overflow\n- `bunx convex dev --once --typecheck=disable` accepted the new schema/index definitions; local push then stopped on unrelated existing `packageReleases.clawScanNote` fixture drift\n\n## Review\n- autoreview clean with no accepted/actionable findings\n- remaining migration/backfill work is intentionally deferred to PR 2\n",
